						<div class="postbody">Oh, that's hilarious. Here I thought the DMG was the one system where you could realistically get away with pure header heuristics alone (with just a bit of nasty voodoo for MMM01 carts.)<br /><br />That even BGB can't run it is deliciously ironic given last year's April Fools joke regarding external mapping information that would solve exactly this problem :P<br /><br />I don't suppose you have any documentation on how the emulated logic needs to change for this alternate wiring? Or have you not emulated it yet either? If not, I may look into it when I get some downtime again.</div>

