						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">byuu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Oh, that's hilarious. Here I thought the DMG was the one system where you could realistically get away with pure header heuristics alone (with just a bit of nasty voodoo for MMM01 carts.)</div><br />It really looks like any system where mappers were used is pretty much doomed to this problem.<br /><br />Reminds me of the suggestion of doing the same with the Mega Drive... As far as licensed games go, you can get away with it because headers contain valid data (aside maybe for a few games with invalid SRAM headers, but those get given away the moment they try to access it). As soon as you enter unlicensed territory you can't trust the ROM anymore since a lot of those have their own custom registers unique to them (ugh!). I really hope people doing homebrew don't attempt to do this because there's still a good chunk of free space in the official header yet &gt;=/ (but good luck getting people to not use the default header their devkit comes with!)</div>

